Narrator

Lileas had invited me here for a private dinner, just the two of us.

Player

"Get to the point, Lileas. Why did you invite me here?"

Lileas Graf

"I wanted you to be the first to know that I myself will be running against you at the Party Congress."

Player

"I forbid you from doing that."

Lileas Graf

"You're a disgrace to the name of Tarquin Soll. Whom, lest we forget, you tried to have imprisoned."

Lileas Graf

"Did you think I'd sit by after you ignored our request to seize power from the Oligarchs?"

Lileas Graf

"You're a disgrace to the good name of Tarquin Soll."

Player

"It's a shame to lose you."

Player

"I understand now why you never found a husband."

Lileas Graf

"Mr. President, I wish I had been consulted on this military parade decision. Is that really the best use of our time and resources given the mounting unrest in this country?"

Player

"Don't worry. The military's taking care of it."

Player

"The military's taking care of it. A little too well, actually."

Lileas Graf

"You and I both know that's not true. Your 'diplomacy' was a disaster."

Lileas Graf

"You gave them authority to act within Sordland's borders. Whatever they do is on your head."

Lileas Graf

"You gave the orders. You can't blame them for doing their job."

Lileas Graf

"That itself is cause for worry."

Lileas Graf

"Mr. President, I'm worried the mounting unrest might hurt our chances of re-election."

Lileas Graf

"The encroaching war with Rumburg certainly doesn't help matters."

Lileas Graf

"A strong leader would ignore the allegations and focus on winning the election. By all means necessary."

Lileas Graf

"Anton, I wish you had made national security more of a top priority during your term."

Lileas Graf

"And I regret that you caved to Ms. Walda and mandated the teaching of that evolution nonsense in schools."

Lileas Graf

"In any event, I'm looking forward to working more closely together during your next term."

Lileas Graf

"Regardless, I'm looking forward to working more closely together during your next term."

Lileas Graf

"I was thrilled when you recognized Sordish schools' right to religious expression over Ms. Walda's ridiculous objections."

Lileas Graf

"I do regret that you caved to Ms. Walda and mandated the teaching of that evolution nonsense in schools."

Lileas Graf

"I don't think the allegations will do much damage, especially with your opposition so weakened. But it's worth keeping an eye on."

Player

"Me too, if it means more excellent dinners like this."

Lileas Graf

"I do wish you had heeded my request to place the Gendarmerie under my jurisdiction."

Lileas Graf

"Likewise, I wish you had heeded my request to place the Gendarmerie under my jurisdiction."

Lileas Graf

"Not to mention feeling the need to pump our children full of strange chemicals in response to some unconfirmed health threat."

Lileas Graf

"However, I'm grateful you defended Sordish citizens' right not to subject their children to mandatory vaccinations."

Lileas Graf

"Likewise, I'm grateful you defended Sordish citizens' right not to subject their children to mandatory vaccinations."

Lileas Graf

"I was less enthused about your decision to pump our children full of strange chemicals in response to some unconfirmed health threat."

Narrator

Lileas raised her glass and smiled.

Lileas Graf

"How are you feeling about that, may I ask?"

Lileas Graf

"I'm a little worried myself. Our national security's still shaky. There may be information leaking to Rumburg from within the Maroon Palace."

Lileas Graf

"Especially with dear Franc in the military."

Narrator

By the end of the meal, I was pleasantly full and a little tipsy. The butler had to lead me back through the manor's winding corridors until I found the door.

Lileas Graf

"Did you think I liked it when you refused to tighten Sordland's borders against disreputable migrants?"

Lileas Graf

"Just stay true to your promise to honor our party's conservative roots, and the good Lord will take care of the rest."

Player

"Enough of this. Lileas, I know about your role in the Bernard Circas murder."

Narrator

She would make a formidable enemy. Thanks to my investigation, I'd managed to dodge that bullet.

Lileas Graf

"Our borders were open to an influx of subversives and refugees that overwhelmed Bergia due to your inability to secure our borders to the west."

Lileas Graf

"The very constitution that is keeping this nation safe from internal and external threats."
